  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Reproductive, Maternal, Newborn and Child Health (RMNCH) services in humanitarian settings.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Action Health Incorporated (AHI) seeks to support life-saving assistance and alleviate suffering through an integrated and coordinated humanitarian response focusing on providing Reproductive, Maternal, Newborn and Child Health (RMNCH) services to the most vulnerable people in hard-to-reach areas in Adamawa State, Nigeria, which is one of the most affected states by the insurgency of the militant group, Boko Haram.  This project will focus on providing RMNCH services to five Local Government Areas namely Fufore,Mubi,Michika,Madagali and Hong which were severely affected by the insurgence with some health facilities completely destroyed and several persons displaced, while many are unaccounted for. At the end of the project cycle, this project design aims to  reduce maternal and child mortality and morbidity in the five LGAs by improving RMNCH Services in the Hotspot LGAs with urgent need of live saving interventions.</narrative>
  </description>
